# lychee ignore patterns — known v1.x-deferred placeholders.
# Each line is a regex matched against the constructed URL.
# When a link in a markdown file resolves to one of these, lychee skips the check.
# Keep this file as small as possible: prefer fixing real broken links over adding ignores.

# Screenshot binaries — Phase 7 docs ship with placeholder paths only.
# Deferred to v1.x per GENERATIONS.md. See CLAUDE.md "What's deferred".
docs/images/.*\.png$

# Curly-brace template placeholders inside templates/brain/ pages —
# these are substituted at provisioning time by R0 / installer.
# Lychee URL-encodes `{{` to `%7B%7B`, so match the encoded form too.
(\{\{|%7B%7B).+(\}\}|%7D%7D)

# Intra-file anchor links in docs/07-troubleshooting.md.
# Headings use a §-prefixed slug convention (§MCP-1 etc.) that GitHub
# renders correctly when humans click but that lychee's slug generator
# does not match. Real navigation works; only the offline check trips.
07-troubleshooting\.md#(mcp|curator|routine|excel|comp|klarna|brain|privacy|secrets|audit)-\d+
